  38,21,"Has the story of the two plaintiffs, who scaled the ňĻwall of David‚Äôsňļ sanctuary, reached you ňĻO Prophetňļ"
  38,22,"When they came into David‚Äôs presence, he was startled by them. They said, ‚ÄúHave no fear. ňĻWe are merelyňļ two in a dispute: one of us has wronged the other. So judge between us with truth‚ÄĒdo not go beyond ňĻitňļ‚ÄĒand guide us to the right way"
  38,23,"This is my brother.¬†He has ninety-nine sheep while I have ňĻonlyňļ one. ňĻStillňļ he asked me to give it up to him, overwhelming me with ňĻhisňļ argument.‚ÄĚ"
  38,24,"David ňĻeventuallyňļ ruled, ‚ÄúHe has definitely wronged you in demanding ňĻto addňļ your sheep to his. And certainly many partners wrong each other, except those who believe and do good‚ÄĒbut how few are they!‚ÄĚ Then David realized that We had tested him so he asked for his Lord‚Äôs forgiveness, fell down in prostration, and turned ňĻto Him in repentanceňļ"
  38,25,So We forgave that for him. And he will indeed have ňĻa status ofňļ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,26,"ňĻWe instructed him:ňļ ‚ÄúO David! We have surely made you an authority in the land, so judge between people with truth. And do not follow ňĻyourňļ desires or they will lead you astray from Allah‚Äôs Way. Surely those who go astray from Allah‚Äôs Way will suffer a severe punishment for neglecting the Day of Reckoning.‚ÄĚ"